432
00:21:16,740 --> 00:21:18,770
♪ To build a castle ♪

433
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,470
♪ Every star is a romantic symbol ♪

434
00:21:21,580 --> 00:21:23,870
♪ Let me find you ♪

435
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:39,090
♪ Even mountains and seas
can't separate us ♪

436
00:21:39,820 --> 00:21:42,870
♪ I wish I could turn into a bird
to explore the world for you ♪

437
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:44,820
♪ The vast, boundless Milky Way ♪

438
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,570
♪ Sings its tender serenade ♪

439
00:21:46,660 --> 00:21:48,910
♪ I can't live a second without you ♪

440
00:21:50,210 --> 00:21:53,480
♪ Looking forward
to the next beautiful dream ♪

441
00:21:53,550 --> 00:21:54,930
♪ I just want to be with you ♪

442
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:58,080
♪ To see the most romantic starry sky
together ♪

443
00:21:58,510 --> 00:22:02,530
♪ The evening breeze tells
heartfelt emotions ♪

444
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:05,080
♪ All the stars surround you ♪

445
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,770
♪ The moon smiles at you ♪

446
00:22:05,180 --> 00:22:06,020
Today, I...

447
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:09,940
♪ I give you all the good things
in the world ♪

448
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:11,970
♪ And the light in your eyes ♪

449
00:22:11,990 --> 00:22:13,980
♪ Shines like diamonds ♪

450
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:17,130
♪ Drawing an exclamation mark
in my world ♪

451
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:15,680
Thank you.

452
00:22:17,250 --> 00:22:18,770
♪ The evening breeze embraces you ♪

453
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:20,540
♪ And I run towards you ♪

454
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:23,890
♪ I hear our passionate heartbeats ♪

455
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:27,720
♪ To build a castle ♪

456
00:22:28,140 --> 00:22:30,470
♪ Every star is a romantic symbol ♪

457
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:33,010
♪ Let me find you ♪

458
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:32,740
Xiaole!

459
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:36,190
I've mastered the photography technique

460
00:22:36,190 --> 00:22:37,850
you taught me last time. Look.

461
00:22:40,740 --> 00:22:42,000
You've improved a lot.

462
00:22:42,020 --> 00:22:44,220
Next, you can try shooting
some night scenes,

463
00:22:44,220 --> 00:22:45,390
work more with Bulb mode,

464
00:22:45,390 --> 00:22:46,350
and take some long-exposure shots.

465
00:22:46,350 --> 00:22:46,740
Okay.

466
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:48,070
Yi Lan?

467
00:22:49,310 --> 00:22:49,910
Manman.

468
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,700
Finished practicing?

469
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:52,180
Yeah.

470
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:54,320
Your club has a lot of activities.

471
00:22:54,650 --> 00:22:55,410
Oh, right,

472
00:22:55,830 --> 00:22:58,390
are you coming to
the outdoor shoot this weekend?

473
00:22:58,390 --> 00:22:59,920
I almost forgot about that.

474
00:23:00,350 --> 00:23:00,870
Sure.

475
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:02,420
I'll contact you then.

476
00:23:02,740 --> 00:23:03,110
Bye.

477
00:23:03,350 --> 00:23:04,020
Bye, Yi Lan.

478
00:23:04,390 --> 00:23:04,940
Bye.

479
00:23:08,390 --> 00:23:11,350
You finished practice pretty early today.

480
00:23:11,660 --> 00:23:13,740
Why were you just standing there quietly
by yourself?

481
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:14,910
No, I just got here.

482
00:23:15,350 --> 00:23:15,940
Let's go.

483
00:23:24,660 --> 00:23:26,420
Mengmeng, can I tell you something?

484
00:23:26,420 --> 00:23:27,110
Go ahead.

485
00:23:29,940 --> 00:23:31,600
Xiaole and I are together now.

486
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:34,830
Who?

487
00:23:35,590 --> 00:23:36,830
Tong Xiaole?

488
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:40,420
I'm mad.

489
00:23:40,870 --> 00:23:41,910
You're mad?

490
00:23:42,830 --> 00:23:44,960
You didn't tell me you two were dating.

491
00:23:45,490 --> 00:23:47,570
You just went through a breakup
over the summer.

492
00:23:47,570 --> 00:23:49,830
I didn't even have the chance to tell you.

493
00:23:49,870 --> 00:23:51,530
Don't be mad anymore, please.

494
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:52,910
I forgive you.

495
00:23:55,260 --> 00:23:57,150
But the way you two are acting...

496
00:23:58,500 --> 00:24:01,220
it doesn't look like
you're in a relationship at all.

497
00:24:01,220 --> 00:24:02,350
What do you mean?

498
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:04,920
You're not with him—

499
00:24:05,260 --> 00:24:07,220
you're here chatting with me instead.

500
00:24:07,220 --> 00:24:07,700
Isn't that because...

501
00:24:07,700 --> 00:24:08,090
you

502
00:24:08,110 --> 00:24:09,390
rarely come to see me?

503
00:24:09,390 --> 00:24:10,850
I should keep you company.

504
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:13,180
Besides, I'm with him every day.

505
00:24:13,180 --> 00:24:14,660
What is there to talk about?

506
00:24:14,660 --> 00:24:16,760
Isn't it because you two have
known each other for too long?

507
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:18,820
Normally, when you're newly dating,

508
00:24:18,870 --> 00:24:20,020
you two should be

509
00:24:20,630 --> 00:24:21,760
all over each other,

510
00:24:21,940 --> 00:24:23,940
not wanting to be apart for a second.

511
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:26,610
Hmm.

512
00:24:27,260 --> 00:24:28,720
-You have a point.
-Right?

513
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,390
Something happened today.

514
00:24:34,180 --> 00:24:35,420
A girl...

515
00:24:35,740 --> 00:24:37,140
wanted to ask Xiaole out.

516
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:37,990
Is that...

517
00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:38,940
okay?

518
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:42,940
A girl?

519
00:24:43,910 --> 00:24:44,970
Asking Xiaole out?

520
00:24:49,510 --> 00:24:51,280
You need to be more alert.

521
00:24:51,630 --> 00:24:53,560
Xiaole is actually quite popular.

522
00:24:58,280 --> 00:25:05,740
[Where are you shooting tomorrow?
Can I come?]

523
00:25:05,740 --> 00:25:11,080
[Sure. See you at
the school gate tomorrow morning.]

524
00:25:35,380 --> 00:25:42,070
[Hailand University;
Truth, Reason, Knowledge, Action]

525
00:25:38,070 --> 00:25:38,660
Xiaole!

526
00:25:39,590 --> 00:25:40,120
Morning.

527
00:25:40,390 --> 00:25:40,920
Morning.

528
00:25:41,020 --> 00:25:42,150
Let's get on the bus.

529
00:25:42,170 --> 00:25:42,970
You go first.

530
00:25:45,420 --> 00:25:47,280
Just go. I'm waiting for someone.

531
00:25:47,460 --> 00:25:47,870
Go.

532
00:25:48,550 --> 00:25:50,080
I'll wait for you on the bus.

533
00:25:51,110 --> 00:25:51,630
Hello.

534
00:25:51,740 --> 00:25:52,420
Morning.

535
00:25:52,740 --> 00:25:53,800
Not getting on yet?

536
00:25:55,460 --> 00:25:56,390
I'm waiting for someone.

537
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:57,190
What's wrong?

538
00:25:59,510 --> 00:26:01,830
Are you joining the photo contest
this time?

539
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:03,760
Probably not, I'm not interested.

540
00:26:03,980 --> 00:26:05,940
There's a photography exhibition
coming up.

541
00:26:05,940 --> 00:26:06,660
Are you interested?

542
00:26:06,660 --> 00:26:07,420
Xiaole!

543
00:26:08,420 --> 00:26:09,150
Morning!

544
00:26:09,350 --> 00:26:10,210
I'm getting on the bus now.

545
00:26:10,210 --> 00:26:10,660
Okay.

546
00:26:10,740 --> 00:26:11,180
Okay.

547
00:26:12,260 --> 00:26:13,420
I'm a bit busy this week.

548
00:26:13,420 --> 00:26:14,750
I'll see about it later.

549
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:19,180
Here.

550
00:26:21,390 --> 00:26:22,850
I'm getting on the bus now.

551
00:26:28,020 --> 00:26:31,150
[Hailand University;
Truth, Reason, Knowledge, Action]

552
00:26:28,350 --> 00:26:29,150
Xiaole...

553
00:26:29,390 --> 00:26:30,260
I'm here!

554
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:32,420
I'm not late, am I?

555
00:26:32,420 --> 00:26:33,220
No.

556
00:26:33,460 --> 00:26:35,150
Why are you carrying your cello?

557
00:26:35,150 --> 00:26:36,680
Just finished practicing.

558
00:26:37,350 --> 00:26:37,940
Alright.

559
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:39,020
Let's go.

560
00:26:40,020 --> 00:26:41,280
Where is Liang Manman?

561
00:26:45,220 --> 00:26:46,420
So many people?

562
00:26:48,220 --> 00:26:48,680
Manman.

563
00:26:49,260 --> 00:26:51,720
What's the relationship between those two?

564
00:26:51,940 --> 00:26:52,800
I asked around.

565
00:26:52,870 --> 00:26:54,130
They grew up together.

566
00:26:54,420 --> 00:26:56,590
I thought it was only the two of you.

567
00:26:56,700 --> 00:26:57,900
How is that possible?

568
00:27:00,390 --> 00:27:03,110
You came because you were worried about
me being alone with her, didn't you?

569
00:27:03,110 --> 00:27:03,660
No!

570
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:04,830
Xiaole!

571
00:27:05,450 --> 00:27:09,050
[Hailand University;
Truth, Reason, Knowledge, Action]

572
00:27:05,940 --> 00:27:07,070
Get on the bus first.

573
00:27:07,740 --> 00:27:08,110
Okay.

574
00:27:08,420 --> 00:27:08,950
Let's go.

575
00:27:09,180 --> 00:27:10,580
There're so many people.

576
00:27:14,940 --> 00:27:16,460
Isn't this a junior
from the music department?

577
00:27:16,460 --> 00:27:16,920
Xiaole,

578
00:27:16,980 --> 00:27:17,830
introduce us.

579
00:27:18,590 --> 00:27:19,220
This is...

580
00:27:19,390 --> 00:27:20,050
Hello, everyone.

581
00:27:20,050 --> 00:27:20,830
I'm Yi Lan.

582
00:27:20,940 --> 00:27:23,350
-Welcome, new friend!
-Welcome, welcome!

583
00:27:31,090 --> 00:27:32,160
Put it here.

584
00:27:36,870 --> 00:27:38,020
I can hold it myself.

585
00:27:38,020 --> 00:27:39,150
It's safer this way.

586
00:27:43,350 --> 00:27:44,480
Sit with me, Xiaole.

587
00:27:48,390 --> 00:27:48,720
Okay.

588
00:27:49,180 --> 00:27:49,700
Thanks.

589
00:27:52,700 --> 00:27:53,350
Driver,

590
00:27:53,660 --> 00:27:55,220
we're all here. Let's go.

591
00:28:12,970 --> 00:28:13,630
Xiaole!

592
00:28:14,180 --> 00:28:15,240
What are you doing?

593
00:28:15,810 --> 00:28:18,320
Did you find any nice compositions?

594
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:19,460
Yes, look.

595
00:28:20,270 --> 00:28:20,750
Okay.

596
00:28:26,690 --> 00:28:27,490
Not bad!

597
00:28:27,990 --> 00:28:29,180
You've gotten

598
00:28:29,180 --> 00:28:31,780
so much better at composition
since last time.

599
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:34,040
It's all thanks to you teaching me.

600
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:35,450
Do you have time now?

601
00:28:35,660 --> 00:28:37,080
Would you like me to show you

602
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:38,410
how to run your account?

603
00:28:42,110 --> 00:28:43,020
Ouch!

604
00:28:43,020 --> 00:28:43,790
What's wrong? What's wrong?

605
00:28:43,790 --> 00:28:44,310
It hurts.

606
00:28:44,310 --> 00:28:44,660
It hurts?

607
00:28:44,660 --> 00:28:45,220
I sprained my ankle.

608
00:28:45,220 --> 00:28:45,770
It really hurts.

609
00:28:45,770 --> 00:28:46,180
You twisted your ankle?

610
00:28:46,180 --> 00:28:47,180
My hand hurts too!

611
00:28:47,870 --> 00:28:48,630
Let me take a look.

612
00:28:48,630 --> 00:28:51,090
You have to blow on it
to make the pain go away.

613
00:28:51,180 --> 00:28:52,150
I have to blow on it?

614
00:28:52,150 --> 00:28:52,700
Mm.

615
00:28:53,660 --> 00:28:55,220
I'll blow on it. Does it feel better?

616
00:28:55,220 --> 00:28:56,180
No more pain, right?

617
00:28:56,180 --> 00:28:57,700
Don't be mad at me anymore.

618
00:28:59,500 --> 00:29:00,650
I'm not mad.

619
00:29:00,740 --> 00:29:01,830
I was wrong.

620
00:29:02,220 --> 00:29:03,940
From now on, I'll always
sit next to you, okay?
